column5: awesome fish bro ...thats a fish of a lifetime ...congrats
Sweet!!! Gotta love catching an incidental muskie like that. 8lb test, must have been a fairly long fight to bring in that 47 incher, she musta weighed about 20-25 lbs easy. Good work!!!

8 pound test!  impressive, Ive hooked into a few while smallie fishin with 8 pound test and every one has taken me hook line and sinker. I happened upon a musky this weekend as well, only it wasnt quite that large...  Cool to get a surprise fish like that

first thing i said it "how the fck am i gonna land this thing" lol  after 15 mins and many runs for the bottem I got my chance at the jaw and went for it !  Luckly I got only a couple scars on my hand !  I got him on a drop shotting rig with a bell sinker and a circle hook... the Line was destroyed after i looked at it .... twists and kinks everywhere... I was lucky to say the least !
A bit of luck, patience and skill I'd say.  Congrats on the PB!!!
very nice!
Beautiful Fish!!  Psst! Did she kiss your boo boo??
haha she better !
Very, Veery Nice ... you got me beat by 4 inches.   Keep on trying ... maybe we'll both hit the 50" club this year.   Congrats to you on your catch, landing, and a good release.
Beauty 'ski man! Don't see too many that size in Haliburton, congrats!
Wow.....  If that thing got near my boat, I'd probably let it take my rod and all... lol  Nice fish...
congrats on the PB...and a great story to go with it!!  dk

Hey all,  Rented a cottage up in the haliburton area for the weekend with my GF.  Planning on quadding saturday and fishing sunday.  Quadding was fun but I was itching to fish since its really been a while since I fished hard on a more remote lake ( compared to simcoe every weekend ).   Nailed 5-6 pike ( 2-5lbs ) throughout the day and my GF landed a nice 2-3 lb bass !! Shes a  Keeper !    Then while working my Yum Dinger I get a hit and BANG set it hard.... I feel dead weight but then it starts to move and all of a sudden this beast rockets to the surface and jumps a couple feet into the air right beside the boat... Gave me and my GF a Heart attack !  Now im freaking since I got 8lb test mono and a size 4 circle hook in this guys Jaws !    after what feels like forever I go for the jaws and lift the monster out ( no net of course !! )    WOW ! 47 inches !!!!    After a couple pics ... I revived the musky until she gave me a splash in the face  well worth it !     Rest of my trip was a blur  .. Now i need a 50 ++
Wow..wouldn't mind having that in my boat!   Nice fish, too.
Congrats on the new PB, she's a beauty  Maureen
What a weekend. You'll both remember that weekend for a while. Congrats! I see that muskie gave your finger a parting kiss as well.
Very nice indeed, congrats on the PB !!
Congrats, great fish...
Congrats on your new pb. Great looking fish.
looks like a great weekend for sure!  cheers!
Nice catch man! SHE IS A BEAUTY
You gota love playing in the mud then have some great fishing, WTG.

Great report/pics and a nice surprise too!!! Musky and dingers/senkos????? Last year the same thing happened to me while fishing for bass with senko style baits. Maybe this is a new bait for Musky(if only it came in a 10 inch version ??????)
Wow, what a great fish!
BEAUTY
Nice Musky!!I was supposed to go up to Haliburton this weekend but cancelled. It looks too far for me! I am now reconsidering!!
Beauty fish!
WOW, now that is a trip and experience that you will remember for the rest of your life! Congratulations.
What a beauty fish!!  Can't beat a weekend of fun in the mud and getting slimed by a musky (and cut by the looks of your finger!)  Good stuff!
What a fish and to land it with 8pnd test. CONGRATS!!!  Cheers, 1leg
wtg, what a fish

One cut on my left hand was from a pike about an hour earlier.. When i went for the Jaw bone on the muskie I got a couple scratches and a nice cut on the other hand. Well worth it !!  Yum dingers !!! a couple pike and the musky on it. No bass touched it !!  Thanks for the comments guys !! I let the beast go with pleasure but got my hooks set DEEP on my women :)lol
Congrats! That's a beautiful fish and a great story (8 lb test!).  Mike
I am so jealous   i so want to catch one of them......WTG...Thats a beauty for  sure.
Wow!! What an amazing report.  8 pound mono...great job landing that beast!!!  Looks like you had an awesome time up there...congrats on the PB...now you gotta go get a 50+ incher!!
Well done. Just goes to show, with a little patience, you can land big fish on light tackle. Congrats.
Wow, great story.  That'll sure get the heart racing.
